[h3]Opportunistic Raiding[/h3]
[list]
[*]New: authorize pop raiding during non-raiding wars by paying 50 Influence. Escalation costs against these targets are doubled.
[*]The prompt appears the first time you bombard each target, not at war declaration, so you're not hit with a stack of popups when war starts.
[*]While opportunistically raiding, you can't switch the war goal, demand tribute, or pivot to pillaging — that's only for real raiding wars.
[/list]

[h3]Balance & Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*]Gestalt empires (Determined Exterminators, Devouring Swarms, etc.) with Nihilistic Acquisition or despoiler civics can now access the Reaping focus.
[*]Nihilistic Acquisition is now hidden for empires that already have a raiding civic.
[*]Fixed a script error when a mercenary enclave event fired without its expected target.
[/list]
